{"cursor":"35761","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n{{Infobox political party |country = Scotland |colorcode = |name = Scottish\nSocialist Party |name_native = PÃ rtaidh SÃ²isealach na h-Alba Scots\nSocialist Pairtie |logo = |leader1_title = National co-convenors |leader1_name =\nColin Fox and Sandra Webster |leader2_title = International co-ordinator\n|leader2_name = Felicity Garvie |foundation = |headquarters = Suite 370, 93 Hope\nStreet  Glasgow  G2 6LD |newspaper = Scottish Socialist Voice\n|youth_wing = Scottish Socialist Youth |wing1_title = Women's wing |wing1 =\nSocialist Women's Network |ideology = Democratic socialism, Feminism, Environmentalism, Scottish independence, Scottish republicanism\n|position = Left-wing |european = European Anticapitalist Left |colours = Red,\nyellow |website = |seats5_title = Local government in Scotland\n|seats5 = }}\n\nThe 'Scottish Socialist Party (SSP)' (; ) is a left-wing Scottish political\nparty. Positioning itself significantly to the left of Scotland's centre-left\nparties, the SSP campaigns on a socialist economic platform and for Scottish\nindependence. It operates through a branch-based structure with additional\nnetworks for identity or campaigning groups, as well as accepting open platforms\nwhich are allowed to organise within the party.\n\nFollowing the 2003 elections to the Scottish Parliament, the party had six\nMembers of the Scottish Parliament (MSPs) and two local councillors. In the 2007\nelections, the SSP lost all of its seats in the Scottish Parliament and retained\nonly one local councillor. In the 2011 elections, the SSP stood in all regional\nlists, however failed to gain any MSPs.\n\nAt the moment, the party campaigns for the establishment of an independent\nScottish socialist republic, for the withdrawal of British troops from\nAfghanistan, and for the provision of free school meals. The party also\ncampaigns against cuts to public services and welfare being introduced by the UK\ngovernment, in particular for the abolition of the bedroom tax and\nfor the government to mitigate fuel poverty caused by soaring fuel\nprices. The party's co-convenor, Colin Fox, holds a position on the\nAdvisory Board of Yes Scotland, the cross-party campaign for Scottish\nindependence in the upcoming referendum.\n","linknr":710,"url":"Scottish_Socialist_Party","recorded":1375084693,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Scottish_Socialist_Party&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Scottish_Socialist_Party&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Scottish_Socialist_Party_(1987%E2%80%931990)","/wiki/File:Scottish_Socialist_Party_logo.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e5/Scottish_Socialist_Party_logo.png/250px-Scottish_Socialist_Party_logo.png","/wiki/Colin_Fox_(politician)","/wiki/Felicity_Garvie","/wiki/Scottish_Socialist_Voice","/wiki/Youth_wing","/wiki/Scottish_Socialist_Youth","/wiki/Socialist_Women%27s_Network","/wiki/List_of_political_ideologies","/wiki/Democratic_socialism","/wiki/Feminism","/wiki/Environmentalism","/wiki/Scottish_independence","/wiki/Scottish_republicanism","/wiki/Political_spectrum","/wiki/Left-wing","/wiki/European_Anticapitalist_Left","/wiki/Red","/wiki/Yellow"